ausing demyelination, which can lead to symptoms like weakness, spasticity, and hyperreflexia.","dimension":15,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.037698,0.056707,0.068591,0.076926,0.088524,0.094698,0.10309,0.10622,0.10337,0.094639,0.089398,0.080144],"unified_progress":[0.048934,0.073507,0.081786,0.088272,0.093464,0.10087,0.098269,0.098823,0.093704,0.087787,0.074697,0.059887]},{"section":13,"text":"The atrophy in the hands and forearms could be due to chronic denervation from upper motor neuron involvement.","dimension":3,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.029179,0.049458,0.067471,0.079528,0.091974,0.099263,0.10586,0.10807,0.10778,0.099473,0.088804,0.073137],"unified_progress":[0.03438,0.061523,0.081038,0.089982,0.097914,0.10225,0.10156,0.10083,0.099473,0.093973,0.077597,0.059472]},{"section":14,"text":"Another possibility is a motor neuron disease like amyotrophic lateral sclerosis (ALS), but ALS usually presents with both upper and lower motor neuron signs, and the atrophy is more widespread, not just in the hands and forearms.","dimension":15,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.028556,0.050255,0.066128,0.077419,0.090045,0.097524,0.10621,0.10933,0.10765,0.10053,0.089976,0.076378],"unified_progress":[0.036486,0.062335,0.078311,0.088826,0.094939,0.10429,0.10118,0.10089,0.097305,0.092517,0.079058,0.063858]},{"section":15,"text":"Plus, the MRI findings in ALS typically don't show such hyperintensity in the cortico-spinal tracts unless there's a specific lesion causing it.","dimension":12,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.032348,0.05055,0.067509,0.079487,0.090727,0.097356,0.10388,0.10549,0.10584,0.099404,0.090614,0.076792],"unified_progress":[0.032222,0.058231,0.07573,0.086363,0.095268,0.10047,0.10039,0.10137,0.10152,0.097486,0.084027,0.066924]},{"section":16,"text":"Could it be a transverse myelopathy?","dimension":5,"group":6,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.022461,0.043766,0.061652,0.076373,0.089861,0.10124,0.11107,0.11494,0.1154,0.10629,0.089982,0.066974],"unified_progress":[0.02844,0.06361,0.083161,0.096378,0.10012,0.10149,0.10442,0.10267,0.098551,0.093488,0.075465,0.05222]},{"section":17,"text":"That could cause weakness and atrophy, but usually affects both legs more prominently and might present with sensory issues as well.","dimension":14,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.035351,0.056017,0.067954,0.075978,0.086434,0.09331,0.10099,0.10546,0.10603,0.099143,0.093419,0.079917],"unified_progress":[0.050967,0.077272,0.083158,0.087025,0.092963,0.098048,0.096733,0.098596,0.09383,0.089413,0.075611,0.056386]},{"section":18,"text":"The hyperreflexia and spasticity in the legs are consistent, but the upper extremity involvement is more pronounced here.","dimension":14,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.0329,0.055516,0.069467,0.077416,0.087654,0.0932,0.098934,0.10191,0.10301,0.097828,0.095368,0.086799],"unified_progress":[0.051737,0.07869,0.085538,0.088764,0.092453,0.096852,0.094101,0.095287,0.091989,0.086184,0.075822,0.062583]},{"section":19,"text":"Inflammatory conditions like acute disseminated encephalomyelitis (ADEM) are possible, but they usually have a more fulminant onset and might involve other symptoms like encephalopathy or more widespread neurological deficits.","dimension":15,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.028192,0.048145,0.063736,0.075479,0.089309,0.097382,0.10861,0.11225,0.10901,0.10167,0.08955,0.076661],"unified_progress":[0.032212,0.058929,0.083896,0.091703,0.097834,0.10952,0.10406,0.10153,0.096842,0.090464,0.074737,0.058279]},{"section":20,"text":"Looking at the pattern of involvement, the upper extremities are more affected with atrophy and weakness, while the lower extremities have spasticity and hyperreflexia.","dimension":14,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.034035,0.057833,0.069121,0.076042,0.085634,0.090929,0.096342,0.099361,0.10068,0.096975,0.098245,0.094805],"u